http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Artificial-limb-distribution/article14022413.ece

Sudheekshan Foundation will distribute LN-4 model artificial hands to persons who have lost their limbs (hands) in accidents, at a function being held here as part of the Road Safety Week. The foundation has proposed to distribute LN-4 hands free of cost to 200 beneficiaries. Police Commissioner Gowtham Sawang and Deputy Transport Commissioner V.Sundhar will give away the artificial limbs to beneficiaries at Vedika Function Hall near Benz Circle. Those who want to benefit from the programme could get more information by calling 8985356811.